table.name: demander_shipping_contracts
table.Comment: The contents of demander shipping contracts are immutable since demander shipping contracts that appear in invalidated_answer_demander_shipping_contracts must never change. Updates on this table are only allowed to change the deactivation_reason, updated_at, and retailer_specific_name fields. Deletions are not allowed.

table.name: invalidated_answer_demander_shipping_contracts
table.Comment: Any update to the set of demander shipping contracts causes re-creation of an answer, so this is always created/invalidated at the same time as the corresponding answer, which is why there is no extra field to specify created_at/invalidated_at.

table.name: item_supplier_shipping_contracts
table.Comment:
Each item can have multiple supplier shipping contracts. This table stores the associations.
Each association has the additional properties of the price at which the item is sold when the corresponding SSC is used.

table.name: items_history
table.Comment: This is unusual in that we put the data points along with their current values instead of previous values. This will make processing easier in that we won't have to also load the items table.

table.name: manufacturer_suggested_retail_prices
table.Comment: This table represents Stockly's knowledge of manufacturer suggested retail prices.

table.name: retailers_last_item_update
table.Comment: This is not in the retailers table because we don't want to rewrite the entire retailers line whenever there is an update - this would introduce contention when just reading the retailers line in other contexts

column.name: name
column.Comment: Permission name (fully qualified name without the domain)

column.name: removed_at_commit
column.Comment: Hash of the commit where the permission was removed

column.name: created_at_commit
column.Comment: Hash of the commit where the permission was created

column.name: removed_at
column.Comment: Time at which the permission was removed from the policy

column.name: removed_at
column.Comment: Time at which the sub-policy was removed from the policy

column.name: github_login
column.Comment: This is what's commonly known as username but named login because that's the term used in github APIs

column.name: promise_to_ship_days
column.Comment:
The expected number of days to ship, based on the supply item/shipping contract we expect to buy for this answer.
Whether this is working or non working days is defined by max_to_ship_is_working_days on the demander_shipping_contract.

column.name: promise_to_deliver_days
column.Comment:
The expected number of days to deliver, based on the supply item/shipping contract we expect to buy for this answer.
Whether this is working or non working days is defined by max_to_deliver_is_working_days on the demander_shipping_contract.

column.name: attr_cost
column.Comment:
The attribution cost of this particular item, for the best supplier shipping contract that we have found for this demander shipping contract.
The attribution cost calculated here is not a cost in the usual common sense (in euros). It is to be intended as a cost in an optimization problem, the opposite of a score (i.e. the goal is to get the lowest possible value for that cost)

column.name: non_promo_price_et
column.Comment: We don't have tolerance on the `price_et <= non_promo_price_et` CHECK because otherwise we might end up having `price_et > non_promo_price_et` after rounding. Stocks is responsible for making sure that never happens by comparing those after having entirely determined `price_et`.

column.name: order_total_lt

column.name: allow_filling
column.Comment: If FALSE, then all answer generation for this demander will be blocked.

column.name: block_filling_percentage
column.Comment:
A value between 0 (inclusive) and 100 (exclusive) indicating the percentage of items that will be blocked during answer generation.
To fully block filling refer to `allow_filling`.

column.name: default_demander_take__flat_amount_et
column.Comment: The default flat amount kept by the demander on item sales. This is neither the flat equivalent of the `default_demander_take__rate_value` nor one of its components: both columns need to be considered as components of the total demander take.

column.name: default_demander_take__rate_value
column.Comment: The default rate kept by the demander on this item's sales, using `demander_take__rate_source` as a source. This is neither the rate equivalent of the `default_demander_take__flat_amount_et` nor one of its components: both columns need to be considered as components of the total demander take.

column.name: demander_take__rate_source
column.Comment: The source to which this demander's take rate should be applied. This is not overridable per item.

column.name: answer_pricing_mode_from
column.Comment: Defines a minimum price for each answer.

column.name: answer_pricing_mode_to
column.Comment:
Defines how high the answer price can be set.
Unless fallback_no_answer is specified, all variants fallback to free pricing if referenced data is not available

column.name: answer_promise_to_ship_add_days_to_expected
column.Comment: The number of days to add to the expected shipping time of the supplier to get the shipping time we'll promise to the demander. This should be NULL if not exported to the demander (if demander doesn't support answer granularity for shipping time promises export, so only demander shipping contracts are relevant). In that case, we will use demander shipping contract max days when exporting the answer.

column.name: answer_promise_to_deliver_add_days_to_expected
column.Comment: The number of days to add to the expected delivery time of the supplier to get the delivery time we'll promise to the demander. This should be NULL if not exported to the demander (if demander doesn't support answer granularity for delivery time promises export, so only demander shipping contracts are relevant). In that case, we will use demander shipping contract max days when exporting the answer.

column.name: promise_to_ship_days
column.Comment:
The expected number of days to ship, based on the supply item/shipping contract we expect to buy for this answer.
Whether this is working or non working days is defined by max_to_ship_is_working_days on the demander_shipping_contract.

column.name: promise_to_deliver_days
column.Comment:
The expected number of days to deliver, based on the supply item/shipping contract we expect to buy for this answer.
Whether this is working or non working days is defined by max_to_deliver_is_working_days on the demander_shipping_contract.

column.name: answer_demander_shipping_contract_id
column.Comment: This may reference an invalidated or not invalidated answer_demander_shipping_contract_id: if an answer supply item is removed from an answer, it will be inserted here regardless of whether the answer itself is invalidated.

column.name: total_price_it
column.Comment: The total price of the competing offer (that is, including shipping), including taxes.

column.name: seller_identifier_value_interned_id
column.Comment: The name of the seller, as they are referred to by the demander. (actual value in interned_strings)

column.name: countries_to_interned_id
column.Comment:
The countries that this price is valid for (that seller may not be selling on all the same countries as we are).
This is actually an ID of the interned_country_list table, to avoid duplications there.

check.name: override_is_not_empty
check.Predicate: (demander_take__rate_value_override IS NOT NULL) OR (demander_take__flat_amount_et_override IS NOT NULL)

column.name: item_distribution_price_et_override
column.Comment:
Overrides the price at which the item is distributed in the network when the corresponding SSC is used.
If not set, and item default_distribution_price_et is not set either, item is not distributed.

column.name: shipping_price_et_override
column.Comment: If set, overrides the price specified by the referenced shipping contract when considering this item.

check.name: items_distributed_price_et_check
check.Predicate: (default_distribution_price_et IS NULL) OR ((default_distribution_price_et <> 'NaN'::double precision) AND (default_distribution_price_et > (0)::double precision))

column.name: default_distribution_price_et
column.Comment:
The price at which the item is distributed in the network, if it is distributed. Distribution price may be overridden by item_distribution_price_et_override in item_supplier_shipping_contracts.
This concept is not to be confused by distributed_price_et, which is for a given item/ssc, the distribution_price of the item when the SSC is used (taking into account the potential override) IFF `distributed` is true.

column.name: demander_take__rate_value_override_if_no_per_country_override
column.Comment: The rate kept by the demander on this item's sales, using the demander's take rate source, if no per-country override is specified. If not specified (and per-country override is not specified either), the demander's default take rate value applies. Please remember that the source on which this rate will be applied will include shipping prices. This is neither the rate equivalent of the `demander_take__flat_amount_et_override` nor one of its components: the sum of the terms for both columns make for the the total demander take.

column.name: demander_take__flat_amount_et_override_if_no_per_country_ovrrde
column.Comment:
demander_take__flat_amount_et_override_if_no_per_country_override
The flat amount kept by the demander on this item's sales, if no per-country override is specified. If not specified (and per-country override is not specified either), the demander's default flat take applies. This is neither the flat equivalent of the `demander_take__rate_value_override` nor one of its components: the sum of the terms for both columns make for the the total demander take.

column.name: distributed
column.Comment: If set to false, item is not distributed. If set to true, item may still not be distributed for different reasons (e.g. neither of default_distribution_price_et and item_distribution_price_et_override being set).

column.name: unable_to_repackage
column.Comment: If true, the item will never be sent to a Repackage center. This may imply that we are not able to sell it: if supplier doesn't provide Neutral packaging, and demander requires neutral packaging

column.name: answer_target_price_upper_bounds_refreshed_at
column.Comment: When the answer_target_price_et_upper_bound was last refreshed, or when the competitors prices set was last refreshed, even if they were refreshed to NULL.

column.name: per_country_demander_take_overrides_input_hash
column.Comment:
A hash of the contents of the `item_demander_takes_per_country` table for this item.
NULL when the table is empty for this item.
This is used to avoid querying the table `item_demander_takes_per_country` table when refreshing items, and possibly when generating answers.
Note that unlike other hashes, (item_characteristics, item_unused_characteristics), NULL does not represent that the hash is not computed, but instead represents that the `item_demander_takes_per_country` table is empty for this item. This allows for lower storage size in the items table when empty (NULL is a single bit), and not querying when empty in answers generation. (So essentially this feature is zero-cost when not used for a given item.)

column.name: competitors_prices_input_hash
column.Comment:
A hash of the contents of the `item_competitors_prices` table for this item.
NULL when the table is empty for this item.
This is used to avoid querying the table `item_competitors_prices` table when refreshing items, and possibly when generating answers.
Note that unlike other hashes, (item_characteristics, item_unused_characteristics), NULL does not represent that the hash is not computed, but instead represents that the `item_competitors_prices` table is empty for this item. This allows for lower storage size in the items table when empty (NULL is a single bit), and not querying when empty in answers generation. (So essentially this feature is zero-cost when not used for a given item.)

column.name: fake_distribution_prices_before_submission_rate
column.Comment:
This will modify the supplier item's total estimated price et (shipping_contract.price_et + item.distributed_price_et), allowing to have an impact on the answer's final price and not only on the selection of one supplier vs. another.
Default is 1, meaning no modification should be applied. Value greater than 1 will penalize the supplier and inversely, value smaller than 1 will act as a booster by generating a lower price.

column.name: restrict_distribution_percentage
column.Comment:
A value between 0 (inclusive) and 100 (exclusive) indicating the percentage of items whose distribution will be restricted. Restriction affects answer generation and purchase creation differently. Please refer to the code for exact behavior.
To fully block distribution refer to `block_distribution_reason`.

column.name: min_item_quantity_for_distribution
column.Comment:
When we have low trust in supplier's stock, we set this to prevent out of stock at submission.
Ultimately this should be handled by the machine-learning approach: WKGSM: Be able to cut volume off to improve cancellation rate because manually setting this is imprecise and supplier-level config is not very granular so this kills volume.

column.name: max_item_weight_kg_for_distribution
column.Comment: This can be used to prevent distribution of heavy/bulky items.
